"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-olympics-2024-what-new-social-media-guidelines-mean-for-athletes-and-their-sponsors-233592\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Junior Lecturer in Mercantile Law, Stellenbosch University Layckan Van Gensen does not work for, consult, own shares in or receive funding from any company or organisation that would benefit from this article, and has disclosed no relevant affiliations beyond their academic appointment.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 288, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Junior Lecturer\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 15}, {\"ngram\": \"Mercantile Law\", \"from\": 19, \"to\": 33}, {\"ngram\": \"Stellenbosch University Layckan Van Gensen\", \"from\": 35, \"to\": 77}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 138}, {\"ngram\": \"any company\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 155}, {\"ngram\": \"organisation\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 171}, {\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 208}, {\"ngram\": \"no relevant affiliations\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 252}, {\"ngram\": \"their academic appointment\", \"from\": 260, \"to\": 286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stellenbosch Universityprovides funding as a partner of The Conversation AFRICA.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 372, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 292, \"end\": 304, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stellenbosch_University\", \"score\": 0.9778290790017715, \"rank\": 0.022673615898890026, \"text\": \"Stellenbosch\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stellenbosch_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stellenbosch_University\"}, {\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3786936408396933e-24, \"text\": \"The Conversation\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a partner\", \"from\": 335, \"to\": 344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners https://doi.org/10.64628/AAJ.qsfgsxw6s Share article Print article Cellphone cameras are ubiquitous at modern sporting events.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all partners\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"https://doi.org/10.64628/AAJ.qsfgsxw6s Share article Print article Cellphone cameras\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"modern sporting events\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 517}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether it's a school swimming gala, the local rugby club squaring off against their bitter rivals or a national team fighting for tournament glory, every moment is a potential photograph.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a school swimming gala\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"the local rugby club\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"their bitter rivals\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 621}, {\"ngram\": \"a national team\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"tournament glory\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 670}, {\"ngram\": \"every moment\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"a potential photograph\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 710}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Games are no exception.More than 10,000 athletes from 200 countries or regionsare set to competein 32 sportsin this year's host city, Paris, giving fans ample opportunity to fill their camera rolls with images of their favourite sporting heroes.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 859, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992707610476, \"rank\": 7.292395916232888e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic Games\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"no exception\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"More than 10,000 athletes\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"200 countries\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 792}, {\"ngram\": \"regionsare\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"32 sportsin\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's host city\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 857}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 877}, {\"ngram\": \"ample opportunity\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"their camera rolls\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"their favourite sporting heroes\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And participants, too, will be able to memorialise their time in Paris - far more freely than ever before.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999992707610476, \"rank\": 7.292395916232888e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"their time\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This comes after the Games' governing body, the International Olympic Committee (IOC), unveilednew social media guidelinesin December 2023.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1127, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games' governing body\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"unveilednew social media guidelinesin\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the guidelines are aimed at athletes; some relate to \\\"accredited individuals other than athletes\\\" such as coaches, technical staff and countries' Olympic committee representatives.\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guidelines\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1264}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"accredited individuals\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"technical staff\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1358}, {\"ngram\": \"countries' Olympic committee representatives\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a legal scholar specialising in sports law, with a focus on image rights, I have been closely following the IOC's stance on athletes' use of social media - especially photographs and videos.Image rightsare a broad bundle which may include rights over the use of the individual's still, moving and animated images, name, signature recorded voice, catch phrases, associated iconic acts, logos, trademark and brands.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a legal scholar\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"sports law\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"image rights\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes' use\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1550}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1566}, {\"ngram\": \"especially photographs\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"Image\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1608}, {\"ngram\": \"a broad bundle\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"rights\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"the individual\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1689}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These rights can be worth a lot of money.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These rights\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1840}, {\"ngram\": \"money\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1868}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, Indiancricketer Virat Kohlican earn anything between US$2 million and US$2.7 million per social media post.\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"Indiancricketer Virat Kohlican\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"social media post\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 1989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, it appears that the IOC has tried to strike a balance between protecting the media rights holders while still recognising the value of a participant's image rights.\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a balance\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"the media rights holders\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2098}, {\"ngram\": \"the value\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2132}, {\"ngram\": \"a participant's image rights\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It allows them to show more content than before and, more importantly, to acknowledge their personal sponsors, who play an important role in commercialising their images and building their brands.\", \"from\": 2166, \"to\": 2362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more content\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2201}, {\"ngram\": \"their personal sponsors\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"an important role\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2303}, {\"ngram\": \"their images\", \"from\": 2323, \"to\": 2335}, {\"ngram\": \"their brands\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loyal fans will get a fuller picture of their favourite athletes' Olympic journeys than they have been able to before.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Loyal fans\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"a fuller picture\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"their favourite athletes' Olympic journeys\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vancouver's 2010 Winter Olympics have been described as \\\"the first social media games\\\", marking the first time that the IOCcreated social media guidelines.\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2483, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"score\": 0.999999997123723, \"rank\": 2.662113475495987e-09, \"text\": \"Vancouver\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vancouver\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first social media games\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2568}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These were refined for theLondon 2012 Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2672, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997744453, \"rank\": 2.2545360788749826e-10, \"text\": \"2012 Summer Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the last Summer Olympics, hosted by Tokyo in 2020, athletes werenot allowed to: share any content from accredited areas used for a sporting competition or ceremony post about their personal sponsors.\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999831743, \"rank\": 1.4520599768494016e-11, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2722}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"any content\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2795}, {\"ngram\": \"accredited areas\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"a sporting competition\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"ceremony post\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2866}, {\"ngram\": \"their personal sponsors\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2896}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These restrictions were designed, the IOCsaid at the time, to protect media rights-holders such as TV stations and other big media organisations.\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These restrictions\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"the IOCsaid\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2946}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 2958}, {\"ngram\": \"media rights-holders\", \"from\": 2971, \"to\": 2991}, {\"ngram\": \"TV stations\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"other big media organisations\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Under the new guidelines accredited participants can share their experiences far more freely on social media platforms during what the IOC calls the \\\"game period\\\", from 18 July to 13 August.\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3183, \"end\": 3186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new guidelines\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3072}, {\"ngram\": \"accredited participants\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3096}, {\"ngram\": \"their experiences\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"social media platforms\", \"from\": 3144, \"to\": 3166}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"game period\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"18 July\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3224}, {\"ngram\": \"13 August\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3237}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They may: take photographs and record audio and video inside and outside the accredited areas share photographs on their personal social media platforms up to one hour before the start of the competition they are taking part in, and after they have left the doping control areas share posts from the training and practice areas, the opening and closing ceremonies and the Champions Park, where athletes gather after their competitions to meet and interact with fans.\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3709, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"photographs\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3266}, {\"ngram\": \"record audio\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3283}, {\"ngram\": \"video\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3293}, {\"ngram\": \"the accredited areas\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3333}, {\"ngram\": \"photographs\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3351}, {\"ngram\": \"their personal social media platforms\", \"from\": 3355, \"to\": 3392}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 3415, \"to\": 3424}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 3428, \"to\": 3443}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3464}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping control areas\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3518}, {\"ngram\": \"posts\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 3530}, {\"ngram\": \"the training and practice areas\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3567}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening and closing ceremonies\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3603}, {\"ngram\": \"the Champions Park\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3634, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"their competitions\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3674}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 3701, \"to\": 3705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course there are still some restrictions.\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some restrictions\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3754}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Videos may not be live streamed, may not be longer than 2 minutes and may not include actual competitions.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3863, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Videos\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3763}, {\"ngram\": \"2 minutes\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3822}, {\"ngram\": \"actual competitions\", \"from\": 3843, \"to\": 3862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, coaches can not film an athlete in action and then share the video or photos.\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3945, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3875}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 3889, \"to\": 3899}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3909}, {\"ngram\": \"the video\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 3934}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3944}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes also can not record another athlete training, or post highlights from their personal competition on social media.\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 4068, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 3954}, {\"ngram\": \"another athlete training\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"post highlights\", \"from\": 4004, \"to\": 4019}, {\"ngram\": \"their personal competition\", \"from\": 4025, \"to\": 4051}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4067}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They can only share such images or videos from official media rights-holders' accounts.\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4156, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such images\", \"from\": 4089, \"to\": 4100}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4110}, {\"ngram\": \"official media rights-holders' accounts\", \"from\": 4116, \"to\": 4155}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps most intriguingly, photographs and videos that use artificial intelligence may not be shared.\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4259, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"artificial intelligence\", \"from\": 4217, \"to\": 4240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's unclear how the IOC intends to police this rule.\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4281, \"end\": 4284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this rule\", \"from\": 4303, \"to\": 4312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Deepfakes in South Africa: protecting your image online is the key to fighting them Media rights-holders are not left completely unprotected by the new guidelines.\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4338, \"end\": 4350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999998226485, \"rank\": 1.677783994816143e-10, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Deepfakes\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4334}, {\"ngram\": \"your image\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4373}, {\"ngram\": \"the key\", \"from\": 4384, \"to\": 4391}, {\"ngram\": \"Media rights-holders\", \"from\": 4409, \"to\": 4429}, {\"ngram\": \"the new guidelines\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Participants are not allowed to post for commercial purposes throughout the game period.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4578, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Participants\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4502}, {\"ngram\": \"commercial purposes\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4550}, {\"ngram\": \"the game period\", \"from\": 4562, \"to\": 4577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A post will be regarded as \\\"for commercial purposes\\\" if its purpose is to generate financial profit or promote any third party or products or services.\", \"from\": 4580, \"to\": 4731, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A post\", \"from\": 4580, \"to\": 4586}, {\"ngram\": \"commercial purposes\", \"from\": 4612, \"to\": 4631}, {\"ngram\": \"its purpose\", \"from\": 4636, \"to\": 4647}, {\"ngram\": \"financial profit\", \"from\": 4663, \"to\": 4679}, {\"ngram\": \"any third party\", \"from\": 4691, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"products\", \"from\": 4710, \"to\": 4718}, {\"ngram\": \"services\", \"from\": 4722, \"to\": 4730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the main goals of the new social media guidelines is to balance the rights of media holders and those of the participants.\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the main goals\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4754}, {\"ngram\": \"the new social media guidelines\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4789}, {\"ngram\": \"the rights\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4814}, {\"ngram\": \"media holders\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4831}, {\"ngram\": \"the participants\", \"from\": 4845, \"to\": 4861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This attempt at a balancing act can be seen in the new rules fornon-Olympic partners- those who do not sponsor or have official merchandise licensing contracts with the IOC.\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 5036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5032, \"end\": 5035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This attempt\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4875}, {\"ngram\": \"a balancing act\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4894}, {\"ngram\": \"the new rules\", \"from\": 4910, \"to\": 4923}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic partners-\", \"from\": 4931, \"to\": 4948}, {\"ngram\": \"official merchandise licensing contracts\", \"from\": 4982, \"to\": 5022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brands or companies in this category may run generic advertising during thegame periodas long as it has not been especially designed for the Olympics and has already been in the public eye for at least 90 days before the tournament starts.\", \"from\": 5038, \"to\": 5277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brands\", \"from\": 5038, \"to\": 5044}, {\"ngram\": \"companies\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5057}, {\"ngram\": \"this category\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5074}, {\"ngram\": \"generic advertising\", \"from\": 5083, \"to\": 5102}, {\"ngram\": \"thegame periodas\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5175, \"to\": 5187}, {\"ngram\": \"the public eye\", \"from\": 5212, \"to\": 5226}, {\"ngram\": \"the tournament\", \"from\": 5255, \"to\": 5269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisements in this category can not be run more frequently during the Games than they have been previously.\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisements\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5292}, {\"ngram\": \"this category\", \"from\": 5296, \"to\": 5309}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC will apply these rules flexibly to enable \\\"business-as-usual\\\" campaigns.\", \"from\": 5390, \"to\": 5470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5394, \"end\": 5397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6675871216545323e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these rules\", \"from\": 5409, \"to\": 5420}, {\"ngram\": \"business-as-usual\\\" campaigns\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Participants are allowed to provide one \\\"thank you\\\" message to each of their non-Olympic partners during the games period but it may not include a personal endorsement.\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5640, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Participants\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5484}, {\"ngram\": \"their non-Olympic partners\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5569}, {\"ngram\": \"the games period\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5593}, {\"ngram\": \"a personal endorsement\", \"from\": 5617, \"to\": 5639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 5642, \"to\": 5696, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2026,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 5642, \"to\": 5696}]}]}"